Otherwise, we should imitate Norway and maintain our economic independence.
The SNP government of Scotland is – and it should be noted – the most successful anti-austerity political movement in Europe, since it won a spectacular majority in 2011 based on its opposition to the dark cuts proposed (and implemented) by the Chancellor of the Labour chessboard, Alistair Darling, and the Conservatives/Coalition.
